    "contentHtml": "<b>A Book of Dances</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\n2024<br />\r\nBook<br />\r\nConcept and edited by Anne Naukkarinen<br />\r\nPublishers Moving in November & TUA - Theatre's New Base Library<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>A Book of Dances</b><i></i> is a collection of written choreographies by Finnish-based artists Anne Naukkarinen (myself), Laura Cemin, Mikko Niemistö, and Marika Peura, and Swedish-based artists BamBam Frost, Ofelia Jarl Ortega, and Pontus Pettersson. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/a-book-of-dances/01.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"837\" width_o=\"1080\" height_o=\"1350\" src_o=\"assets/projects/a-book-of-dances/01.jpg\" data-mid=\"79941657\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 837\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/a-book-of-dances/01.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe book explores language as a writing-based approach to choreographic practice. It brings attention to the contradictions, translations, and intimate relationships between dance and language. In A Book of Dances, multiple languages are intertwined with the situated knowledge and histories of the participating artists, each embedded within specific social contexts.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe book’s aim is not to define choreographic practices as such, but to create a space for writing that engages with and embodies diverse perspectives on world-making. Thus, the process of meaning-making becomes situated, relational, and unstable—it shifts constantly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Credits</b><br />\r\nConcept: Anne Naukkarinen  <br />\r\nWriters: Laura Cemin, BamBam Frost, Anne Naukkarinen, Mikko Niemistö, Ofelia Jarl Ortega, Pontus Pettersson and Marika Peura  <br />\r\nTranslator: Carmen Baltzar   <br />\r\nPublishers: Teatterin Uusi Alkukirjasto T/U/A & Moving in November  <br />\r\nEditors: Anne Naukkarinen and T/U/A  <br />\r\nAD: Aino Nieminen / Last Tuesday Oy  <br />\r\nProduction: Anne Naukkarinen and Moving in November  <br />\r\nBook launches: Moving in November -festival at Kunsthalle Helsinki and MDT Moderna Dansteattern in collaboration with höjden studios, Sweden<br />\r\nResidency: Zodiak – Center For New Dance  <br />\r\nSupporters: Wihuri Foundation, Teaterstiftelsen Vivicas Vänner, Finnish Cultural Foundation, Arts Promotion Centre Finland, Oskar Öflund Stiftelse, and Kone Foundation  <br />\r\nImage: Aino Nieminen<br />\r\nProofreading and language advice in marketing text: Katie Lenanton  <br />\r\nThank you Laura Cemin, Tiago Martins Pinto, Olga Spyropoulou, Maria Kojonen and Riikka Thitz for the artistic dialogues. <br />\r\nVisit in collaboration: Kunsthalle Helsinki<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>A Book of Dances</b> is available at the following locations:<br />\r\nNide (Fredrikinkatu 35, Helsinki)<br />\r\nRosebud Sivullinen (Kaisaniemenkatu 35, Helsinki)<br />\r\nPp. at the House of Text (Lintulahdenkatu 3, Helsinki)<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.norma-t.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Norma T</a>, Oslo<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://tuakirjasto.fi/shop/\" target=\"_blank\">Tuakirjasto.fi</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.suomalainen.com/products/book-of-dances-a?queryId=6e2bb5c222274473eab6751985f65dbd&objectId=53704721334607\" target=\"_blank\">Suomalainen kirjakauppa</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can also buy a book from me by directly contacting!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Articles and Interviews</b><br />\r\nWihuri Foundation's <a href=\"https://wihurinrahasto.fi/media-arkisto/kirjoitettuja-koreografioita-nain-syntyi-a-book-of-dances-teos/\" target=\"_blank\">Article</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://movinginnovember.fi/conversation-between-anne-naukkarinen-and-kerstin-schroth-about-a-book-of-dances/\" target=\"_blank\">Conversation</a> between Anne Naukkarinen and Kerstin Schroth about A Book of Dances <br />\r\nTheatre’s New Base Library <a href=\"https://tuakirjasto.fi/2024/10/7-written-choreographies-a-book-of-dances-is-published-on-november-10th/\" target=\"_blank\">Interview</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "A Book of Dances\n\n2024\nBook\nConcept and edited by Anne Naukkarinen\nPublishers Moving in November & TUA - Theatre's New Base Library\n\nA Book of Dances is a collection of written choreographies by Finnish-based artists Anne Naukkarinen (myself), Laura Cemin, Mikko Niemistö, and Marika Peura, and Swedish-based artists BamBam Frost, Ofelia Jarl Ortega, and Pontus Pettersson. \n\n{image 1}\n\nThe book explores language as a writing-based approach to choreographic practice. It brings attention to the contradictions, translations, and intimate relationships between dance and language. In A Book of Dances, multiple languages are intertwined with the situated knowledge and histories of the participating artists, each embedded within specific social contexts.\n\nThe book’s aim is not to define choreographic practices as such, but to create a space for writing that engages with and embodies diverse perspectives on world-making. Thus, the process of meaning-making becomes situated, relational, and unstable—it shifts constantly.\n\nCredits\nConcept: Anne Naukkarinen  \nWriters: Laura Cemin, BamBam Frost, Anne Naukkarinen, Mikko Niemistö, Ofelia Jarl Ortega, Pontus Pettersson and Marika Peura  \nTranslator: Carmen Baltzar   \nPublishers: Teatterin Uusi Alkukirjasto T/U/A & Moving in November  \nEditors: Anne Naukkarinen and T/U/A  \nAD: Aino Nieminen / Last Tuesday Oy  \nProduction: Anne Naukkarinen and Moving in November  \nBook launches: Moving in November -festival at Kunsthalle Helsinki and MDT Moderna Dansteattern in collaboration with höjden studios, Sweden\nResidency: Zodiak – Center For New Dance  \nSupporters: Wihuri Foundation, Teaterstiftelsen Vivicas Vänner, Finnish Cultural Foundation, Arts Promotion Centre Finland, Oskar Öflund Stiftelse, and Kone Foundation  \nImage: Aino Nieminen\nProofreading and language advice in marketing text: Katie Lenanton  \nThank you Laura Cemin, Tiago Martins Pinto, Olga Spyropoulou, Maria Kojonen and Riikka Thitz for the artistic dialogues. \nVisit in collaboration: Kunsthalle Helsinki\n\nA Book of Dances is available at the following locations:\nNide (Fredrikinkatu 35, Helsinki)\nRosebud Sivullinen (Kaisaniemenkatu 35, Helsinki)\nPp. at the House of Text (Lintulahdenkatu 3, Helsinki)\nNorma T, Oslo\nTuakirjasto.fi\nSuomalainen kirjakauppa\n\nYou can also buy a book from me by directly contacting!\n\nArticles and Interviews\nWihuri Foundation's Article\nConversation between Anne Naukkarinen and Kerstin Schroth about A Book of Dances \nTheatre’s New Base Library Interview",
