    "contentHtml": "<b>how to ________ alone</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2018 & 2019<br />\r\nPerformance <br />\r\nInstallation (stage, sound technique, 60 T-shirts)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/01.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/01.jpg\" data-mid=\"73004496\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/01.jpg\" /> <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<i> how to ________ alone</i> performance looks at the relations between the art worker, the work of the artist, and the work of art in the form of a durational performance, a gig. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOn YouTube, I watched philosopher and performance art theorist Bojana Kunst’s lecture, Artist at Work, which is based on the book, <i>Proximity of Art and Capitalism</i>. Kunst mentions that the artist of today is a collaborative, nomadic wanderer, a networker who is perpetually working. However, the artist works in seclusion and at a distance from others, inside a kind of protective circle. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring the working process of <i>how to __________ alone</i>, I made observations that made me consider my relations to the individualistic art worker that our culture has created. Along with the creative work, my work entailed communication, marketing, scheduling, meetings, emotional labour and other art related tasks. I wondered how to relate with it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Performances</b><br />\r\n5.5.-3.6.2018, Kuvat Kevät 2018, MFA Degree Show of the Academy of Fine Arts, Helsinki, Finland<br />\r\n30.3.-26.5.2019, Young Artist 2019 Exhibition, Taidehalli Helsinki, Finland<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Credits</b><br />\r\nChoreography, concept, performing: Anne Naukkarinen<br />\r\nLight design: Sofia Palillo<br />\r\nSound design: Antti Kainulainen<br />\r\nSupervisor: Maija Mustonen<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/02.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/02.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726698\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/02.jpg\" /> <img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/03.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/03.jpg\" data-mid=\"72868502\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/03.jpg\" /><img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/04.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/04.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726703\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/04.jpg\" /><img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/05.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"1005\" width_o=\"1606\" height_o=\"2409\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/05.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726697\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 1005\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/05.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/06.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/06.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726704\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/06.jpg\" /><img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/07.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/07.jpg\" data-mid=\"72868491\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/07.jpg\" /><img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/08.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"1005\" width_o=\"1606\" height_o=\"2409\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/08.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726701\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 1005\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/08.jpg\" /><img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/09.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/09.jpg\" data-mid=\"72726708\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/09.jpg\" /> <img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/10.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"2409\" height_o=\"1606\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/10.jpg\" data-mid=\"72868499\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/10.jpg\" /> Photos: Maarit Mustonen<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<i>how to ________ alone </i> performance was selected to be part of the <i>Young Artists 2019</i> exhibition at Taidehalli museum. Read more about the <a href=\"https://taidehalli.fi/en/events/young-artists-2019/\" target=\"_blank\"><b>Young Artists 2019</b></a> exhibition. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/11.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"447\" width_o=\"1875\" height_o=\"1251\" src_o=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/11.jpg\" data-mid=\"74928780\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 447\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/how-to-alone/11.jpg\" /><br />\r\nImage: Patrik Rastenberger/Taidehalli<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.artandaustralia.com/online/online/dispatches/helsinki.html\" target=\"_blank\">Review </a>of <i>how to ________  alone</i> performance by <a href=\"https://jessiebullivant.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Jessie Bullivant </a>on A+A Online Magazine.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n_____<br />\r\n<br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "how to ________ alone\n\n2018 & 2019\nPerformance \nInstallation (stage, sound technique, 60 T-shirts)\n\n{image 17} \n\n how to ________ alone performance looks at the relations between the art worker, the work of the artist, and the work of art in the form of a durational performance, a gig. \n\nOn YouTube, I watched philosopher and performance art theorist Bojana Kunst’s lecture, Artist at Work, which is based on the book, Proximity of Art and Capitalism. Kunst mentions that the artist of today is a collaborative, nomadic wanderer, a networker who is perpetually working. However, the artist works in seclusion and at a distance from others, inside a kind of protective circle. \n\nDuring the working process of how to __________ alone, I made observations that made me consider my relations to the individualistic art worker that our culture has created. Along with the creative work, my work entailed communication, marketing, scheduling, meetings, emotional labour and other art related tasks. I wondered how to relate with it.\n\nPerformances\n5.5.-3.6.2018, Kuvat Kevät 2018, MFA Degree Show of the Academy of Fine Arts, Helsinki, Finland\n30.3.-26.5.2019, Young Artist 2019 Exhibition, Taidehalli Helsinki, Finland\n\nCredits\nChoreography, concept, performing: Anne Naukkarinen\nLight design: Sofia Palillo\nSound design: Antti Kainulainen\nSupervisor: Maija Mustonen\n\n{image 6} {image 16}{image 9}{image 5}\n{image 10}{image 14}{image 8}{image 12} {image 15} Photos: Maarit Mustonen\n\nhow to ________ alone  performance was selected to be part of the Young Artists 2019 exhibition at Taidehalli museum. Read more about the Young Artists 2019 exhibition. \n\n{image 18}\nImage: Patrik Rastenberger/Taidehalli\n\nReview of how to ________  alone performance by Jessie Bullivant on A+A Online Magazine.\n\n_____",
