    "shortDescription": "WATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we ",
    "fullDescription": [
      "WATER FALL 6",
      "2017\nPerformance (40 min)\nwith Maarit Mustonen",
      "{image 2}",
      "WATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. WATER FALL 6 was performed at the XS Vol. 9 - Festival for New Dance and Performance, Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku.",
      "{image 4}"
    ],
    "contentHtml": "<b>WATER FALL 6</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\n2017<br />\r\nPerformance (40 min)<br />\r\nwith Maarit Mustonen<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/01.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"3402\" height_o=\"2268\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/01.jpg\" data-mid=\"74870007\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/01.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. WATER FALL 6 was performed at the XS Vol. 9 - Festival for New Dance and Performance, Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/02.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"463\" width_o=\"3402\" height_o=\"2351\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/02.jpg\" data-mid=\"74870011\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 463\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-6/02.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "WATER FALL 6\n\n2017\nPerformance (40 min)\nwith Maarit Mustonen\n\n{image 2}\n\nWATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. WATER FALL 6 was performed at the XS Vol. 9 - Festival for New Dance and Performance, Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku.\n\n{image 4}",
