    "shortDescription": "WATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016 with WATER FALL 1. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element.",
    "fullDescription": [
      "WATER FALL 1 ",
      "2016\nPerformance (35 min)\nwith Maarit Mustonen",
      "{image 13}",
      "WATER FALL 1 at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku, 29 October 2016.",
      "WATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016 with WATER FALL 1. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. The WATER FALL 1 was performed at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo in Turku.",
      "{image 14}\n{image 11}\n{image 15}\n{image 12} \n{image 9}\nPhotos: Hertta Kiiski"
    ],
    "contentHtml": "<b>WATER FALL 1 </b><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2016<br />\r\nPerformance (35 min)<br />\r\nwith Maarit Mustonen<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/01.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"3543\" height_o=\"2362\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/01.jpg\" data-mid=\"72090328\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/01.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWATER FALL 1 at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku, 29 October 2016.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016 with WATER FALL 1. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. The WATER FALL 1 was performed at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo in Turku.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/02.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"1005\" width_o=\"2362\" height_o=\"3543\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/02.jpg\" data-mid=\"72090330\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 1005\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/02.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/03.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"3543\" height_o=\"2362\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/03.jpg\" data-mid=\"69674322\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/03.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/04.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"1005\" width_o=\"2362\" height_o=\"3543\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/04.jpg\" data-mid=\"72090332\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 1005\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/04.jpg\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/05.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"3543\" height_o=\"2362\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/05.jpg\" data-mid=\"72090326\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/05.jpg\" /> <br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/06.jpg\" width=\"670\" height=\"446\" width_o=\"3543\" height_o=\"2362\" src_o=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/06.jpg\" data-mid=\"69674289\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 446\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/water-fall-1/06.jpg\" /><br />\r\nPhotos: Hertta Kiiski<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n <br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "WATER FALL 1 \n\n2016\nPerformance (35 min)\nwith Maarit Mustonen\n\n{image 13}\n\nWATER FALL 1 at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo, Turku, 29 October 2016.\n\nWATER FALL, a series of performances and installations began in 2016 with WATER FALL 1. The series aimed to explore bodily and verbal fluidity and imagination, with particular emphasis on the motion of the water element. In the series we looked at water as material - melting ice, boiling water, water in the bodies, but also we explored locations associated with water like swimming pools, lakes and seas. The WATER FALL 1 was performed at Contemporary Art Space Kutomo in Turku.\n\n{image 14}\n{image 11}\n{image 15}\n{image 12} \n{image 9}\nPhotos: Hertta Kiiski",
