    "contentHtml": "<b>Translator's Note</b><br />\r\n<b>(Nota del traduttore)</b><br />\r\n<br />\r\n <br />\r\n2015<br />\r\nPerformance<br />\r\n10 min<br />\r\nLanguage: Italian<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n <img src=\"assets/projects/translators-note/01.png\" width=\"670\" height=\"439\" width_o=\"2260\" height_o=\"1482\" src_o=\"assets/projects/translators-note/01.png\" data-mid=\"79227728\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 439\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/translators-note/01.png\" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<i>Translator`s Note</i> is a piece for two performers, a dancer and a reader. The dancer listens to an Italian monologue read by the other performer, she moves in relation to it and the reader. The dancer knows neither Italian language, nor the content of the text. The movement material of the dancer has been created by examining the experiences of not-knowing. The monologue of the piece plays with the absence and the presence of the writer in the performance situation.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTranslator's Note was performed at the group exhibition The Sense of the Body at Accademia Albertina, Turin (IT), in 2015.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn collaboration with:<br />\r\nMaarit Mustonen – concept, writer<br />\r\nAnne Naukkarinen – dancer, choreographer<br />\r\nValentina Roselli – performer, reader<br />\r\nKatja Mäkkylä – Finnish-Italian translation and assistance in Helsinki<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe work was supported by Finnish Academy of Fine Arts / University of the Arts Helsinki<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/translators-note/02.png\" width=\"670\" height=\"440\" width_o=\"2256\" height_o=\"1484\" src_o=\"assets/projects/translators-note/02.png\" data-mid=\"79227730\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 440\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/translators-note/02.png\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/translators-note/03.png\" width=\"670\" height=\"441\" width_o=\"2260\" height_o=\"1488\" src_o=\"assets/projects/translators-note/03.png\" data-mid=\"79227731\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 441\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/translators-note/03.png\" /><br />\r\n<img src=\"assets/projects/translators-note/04.png\" width=\"670\" height=\"442\" width_o=\"2264\" height_o=\"1496\" src_o=\"assets/projects/translators-note/04.png\" data-mid=\"79227729\" border=\"0\" align=\"left\" data-title=\"670 — 670 × 442\"data-hi-res=\"assets/projects/translators-note/04.png\" /><br />\r\nDocumentation: Maarit Mustonen<br />\r\n<br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "Translator's Note\n(Nota del traduttore)\n\n \n2015\nPerformance\n10 min\nLanguage: Italian\n\n {image 5}\n\nTranslator`s Note is a piece for two performers, a dancer and a reader. The dancer listens to an Italian monologue read by the other performer, she moves in relation to it and the reader. The dancer knows neither Italian language, nor the content of the text. The movement material of the dancer has been created by examining the experiences of not-knowing. The monologue of the piece plays with the absence and the presence of the writer in the performance situation.\n\nTranslator's Note was performed at the group exhibition The Sense of the Body at Accademia Albertina, Turin (IT), in 2015.\n\nIn collaboration with:\nMaarit Mustonen – concept, writer\nAnne Naukkarinen – dancer, choreographer\nValentina Roselli – performer, reader\nKatja Mäkkylä – Finnish-Italian translation and assistance in Helsinki\n\nThe work was supported by Finnish Academy of Fine Arts / University of the Arts Helsinki\n\n{image 7}\n{image 8}\n{image 6}\nDocumentation: Maarit Mustonen",
