    "shortDescription": "Anne Naukkarinen (b. 1987) is a Helsinki-based choreographer and visual artist working at the intersections of performance art, choreography, and visual arts. In her artworks, she explores intimate and complex human expe",
    "fullDescription": [
      "Anne Naukkarinen (b. 1987) is a Helsinki-based choreographer and visual artist working at the intersections of performance art, choreography, and visual arts. In her artworks, she explores intimate and complex human experiences—emotions, affects, sensations, and thoughts in motion, always in relation to specific situations and environments. Her methods draw from dance and somatic practices, and writing. ",
      "Naukkarinen has created works for dance, performance, and visual arts contexts, as well as for site-specific locations. Her recent works have been presented at e.g. Moving in November, Moderna Dansteatern – MDT, Mad House Helsinki, Titanik Gallery, SIC Gallery, Kunsthalle Helsinki, and Contemporary Art Space Kutomo. Naukkarinen is currently creating a new site-responsive artwork Jousikvartetto commissioned by curator Riikka Thitz and i dolci.",
      "She holds a Master of Fine Arts from the Academy of Fine Arts, Helsinki (2020), and a Bachelor’s degree in Dance from the Theatre Academy, Helsinki (2015). She also studied at the Inter-University Centre for Dance Berlin (HZT) in 2014.",
      "anne.naukkar@gmail.com\nIG: annenaukkarinen"
    ],
    "contentHtml": "<b>Anne Naukkarinen</b> (b. 1987) is a Helsinki-based choreographer and visual artist working at the intersections of performance art, choreography, and visual arts. In her artworks, she explores intimate and complex human experiences—emotions, affects, sensations, and thoughts in motion, always in relation to specific situations and environments. Her methods draw from dance and somatic practices, and writing. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nNaukkarinen has created works for dance, performance, and visual arts contexts, as well as for site-specific locations. Her recent works have been presented at e.g. Moving in November, Moderna Dansteatern – MDT, Mad House Helsinki, Titanik Gallery, SIC Gallery, Kunsthalle Helsinki, and Contemporary Art Space Kutomo. Naukkarinen is currently creating a new site-responsive artwork Jousikvartetto commissioned by curator Riikka Thitz and i dolci.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nShe holds a Master of Fine Arts from the Academy of Fine Arts, Helsinki (2020), and a Bachelor’s degree in Dance from the Theatre Academy, Helsinki (2015). She also studied at the Inter-University Centre for Dance Berlin (HZT) in 2014.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<i>anne.naukkar@gmail.com</i><br />\r\n<i>IG: annenaukkarinen</i><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n",
    "contentText": "Anne Naukkarinen (b. 1987) is a Helsinki-based choreographer and visual artist working at the intersections of performance art, choreography, and visual arts. In her artworks, she explores intimate and complex human experiences—emotions, affects, sensations, and thoughts in motion, always in relation to specific situations and environments. Her methods draw from dance and somatic practices, and writing. \n\nNaukkarinen has created works for dance, performance, and visual arts contexts, as well as for site-specific locations. Her recent works have been presented at e.g. Moving in November, Moderna Dansteatern – MDT, Mad House Helsinki, Titanik Gallery, SIC Gallery, Kunsthalle Helsinki, and Contemporary Art Space Kutomo. Naukkarinen is currently creating a new site-responsive artwork Jousikvartetto commissioned by curator Riikka Thitz and i dolci.\n\nShe holds a Master of Fine Arts from the Academy of Fine Arts, Helsinki (2020), and a Bachelor’s degree in Dance from the Theatre Academy, Helsinki (2015). She also studied at the Inter-University Centre for Dance Berlin (HZT) in 2014.\n\nanne.naukkar@gmail.com\nIG: annenaukkarinen",
